Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.50,0:00:07.42,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,We're almost done with this area.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.42,0:00:09.20,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,We missed two platoons or so.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.20,0:00:10.20,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Watch for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.47,0:00:11.74,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.00,0:00:13.85,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Message from Naotsugu.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.85,0:00:16.14,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,The enemy might be approaching.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.14,0:00:17.99,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,I'll report once I have visual.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.16,0:00:19.20,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Tohya!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.20,0:00:21.00,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Lure them out! Got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.32,0:00:25.88,Default,Re,0000,0000,0000,,But how far can Miss Minori \Nsee in this darkness?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.88,0:00:29.25,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,She's using magic eye drops \Nthat Naotsugu lent her.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.71,0:00:33.01,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,She should be able to see \Nlike a cat for a full day.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.50,0:00:36.11,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,So far, it's all gone according to plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.11,0:00:37.51,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,It has to go well.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.22,0:00:41.32,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,I forced everyone into agreeing with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.10,0:00:43.71,Default - flashback,M,0000,0000,0000,,A night attack?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.71,0:00:45.15,Default - flashback,M,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.15,0:00:47.42,Default - flashback,M,0000,0000,0000,,You said you were just getting \Nthem to evacuate!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.42,0:00:49.62,Default - flashback,M,0000,0000,0000,,Those kids can't protect the city alone...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.62,0:00:52.69,Default - flashback,N,0000,0000,0000,,No, they didn't say they could.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.69,0:00:54.65,Default - flashback,N,0000,0000,0000,,That's why they're attacking.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.92,0:00:55.60,Default - flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.60,0:00:57.93,Default - flashback,N,0000,0000,0000,,The goblins aren't protecting anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.93,0:01:00.91,Default - flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,If we worry about protecting \Nsomething, we can't beat them.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.28,0:01:02.64,Default - flashback,N,0000,0000,0000,,So we attack them.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.64,0:01:03.63,Default - flashback,N,0000,0000,0000,,That's the plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.63,0:01:04.96,Default - flashback,M,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.96,0:01:07.74,Default - flashback,N,0000,0000,0000,,And when they're attacked, they'll get spooked.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.12,0:01:12.01,Default - flashback,N,0000,0000,0000,,They aren't well-trained, \Nso that'll slow them down.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.01,0:01:16.43,Default - flashback,N,0000,0000,0000,,And their attacks will be more sporadic \Nand more easily defended.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.35,0:01:20.93,Default - flashback,N,0000,0000,0000,,Honestly, it isn't a bad strategy.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.86,0:01:23.99,Default - flashback,N,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.99,0:01:26.19,Default - flashback,N,0000,0000,0000,,We'll be with them. Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.03,0:01:34.05,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,It's going to be a long night.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.05,0:01:34.96,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.96,0:01:37.32,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,But we aren't alone, are we?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.79,0:01:40.07,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,As long as they have something \Nto protect, anyone would...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.80,0:01:45.58,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Marie tells me they're going \Nto be defending Choushu.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.05,0:01:49.03,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Naotsugu and his group are \Npreparing a surprise attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.03,0:01:52.84,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,What? We haven't even finished \Ndiscussing things here.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.21,0:01:55.47,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,If you were actually there, seeing it,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.47,0:01:57.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you naturally wouldn't want to just ignore it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.20,0:02:03.60,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,The three of us hold all power over decisions in \Nthis matter, which includes sending troops.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.03,0:02:08.40,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,We must quickly come to a consensus \Nbefore the next full conference.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.66,0:03:41.95,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,A plot?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.95,0:03:46.24,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,You're saying the goblin attack \Nis an adventurer plot?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.58,0:03:52.00,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,If the adventurers had acted to weaken them \Nfrom the start, this wouldn't have happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.23,0:03:56.15,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Though I think calling it a plot \Nis a rather drastic leap...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.15,0:03:57.75,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Baron Krendit,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.05,0:04:01.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,right now, it's important that no \None withhold their thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.03,0:04:06.05,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that why we've held this \Nconference without them?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.28,0:04:11.02,Default,Guy43,0000,0000,0000,,To be honest, I don't expect \NChoushu to last for long.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.49,0:04:15.25,Default,Guy43,0000,0000,0000,,Most likely, their next target will be \NTsukuba, Lord Kiliva's territory.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.44,0:04:17.90,Default,Guy43,0000,0000,0000,,Or possibly...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.97,0:04:21.15,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Maihama?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.19,0:04:27.16,Title,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1823,1)}A Lazy, Cowardly Princess
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.84,0:04:24.92,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,A Lazy, Cowardly Princess.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.37,0:04:28.70,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.70,0:04:31.06,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Are they still having their little secret meeting?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.06,0:04:35.17,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,It's probably about something they \Nreally don't want us to hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.49,0:04:37.46,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,They haven't settled on a course of action,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.46,0:04:39.43,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,and they have to consider their pride.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.43,0:04:42.17,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,They'd prefer not to owe \Nthe adventurers anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.39,0:04:45.75,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,The first group they're likely to turn to is...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.75,0:04:49.53,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, the guardians they've held in \Nhigh esteem since ancient times...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.53,0:04:51.05,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,The Izumo Knights.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.56,0:04:52.46,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.96,0:04:54.18,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,Then, as we thought...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.92,0:04:58.05,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, none of us has any idea why,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.05,0:05:01.07,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,but the Knights of Izumo are gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.26,0:05:05.68,Default,Guy3,0000,0000,0000,,Our recon teams report
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.68,0:05:10.08,Default,Guy3,0000,0000,0000,,that several of the fortresses \Nthey once used are empty.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.33,0:05:15.08,Default,Guy3,0000,0000,0000,,And they found no corpses or signs of combat.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.34,0:05:17.59,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,It's as if they've been spirited away.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.59,0:05:21.09,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,But in any case, the fact is that they're gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.33,0:05:28.09,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,Th-Then our only hope is for all the lords \Nto unite and attack the goblins...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.09,0:05:29.35,Default,Guy4,0000,0000,0000,,Strategically speaking,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.35,0:05:33.12,Default,Guy4,0000,0000,0000,,surrounding them is the most feasible plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.12,0:05:36.25,Default,Guy4,0000,0000,0000,,We force them to lay siege to \Na well-defended stronghold city,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.25,0:05:41.11,Default,Guy4,0000,0000,0000,,and when they're tired, we surround them \Nwith a large, combined army, and attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.40,0:05:42.44,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.44,0:05:48.04,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,That sounds like you're telling us \Nto sacrifice one of the cities.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.77,0:05:49.62,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,You aren't...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.01,0:05:54.93,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,going to tell me to sacrifice Tsukuba since \Nit's the one they're likely to target, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.93,0:05:57.37,Default,Guy3,0000,0000,0000,,No, no one's saying that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.37,0:05:58.70,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,Of course not!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.70,0:06:01.13,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,I won't let Tsukuba be sacrificed!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.36,0:06:04.63,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Calm down, Lord Kiliva.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.15,0:06:07.13,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Let's take a break.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.16,0:06:16.14,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,They're approaching!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.14,0:06:17.28,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Two platoons.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.28,0:06:18.83,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Ten or so...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.83,0:06:21.15,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Tohya's succeeded in luring them out.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.43,0:06:22.23,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.23,0:06:24.02,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Start the countdown!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.22,0:06:25.18,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Five,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.18,0:06:26.23,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,four,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.23,0:06:27.03,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,three,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.26,0:06:28.26,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,two,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.26,0:06:29.21,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,one...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.21,0:06:29.84,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Zero!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.02,0:06:35.79,Default - italics,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Willow Spirits!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.04,0:06:39.21,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,I've rooted them!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.21,0:06:40.04,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.27,0:06:41.23,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Here I go.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.23,0:06:43.21,Default - italics,R,0000,0000,0000,,Icicle Blade!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.70,0:06:45.55,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Rudy!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.91,0:06:48.49,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Save your big spells and \Nattack small-scale for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.49,0:06:49.99,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,I'll back you up for thirty seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.99,0:06:50.68,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.68,0:06:52.73,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Second wave at two o'clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.58,0:06:55.22,Default - italics,R,0000,0000,0000,,Flare Arrow!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.69,0:06:59.48,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,Maestro Echo!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.97,0:07:06.97,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Wonderful, Miss Isuzu.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.97,0:07:08.00,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Not now!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.51,0:07:11.98,HUD1,I,0000,0000,0000,,{\an9}Seconds Left
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.00,0:07:10.63,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Once your cool down finishes, attack again!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.63,0:07:11.99,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Leave it to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.77,0:07:19.50,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,If they aren't able to rely on the Izumo Knights...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.79,0:07:24.00,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,That would make us their only other option.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.53,0:07:27.05,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,As long as we're here, in this world,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.48,0:07:30.28,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,we won't be able to avoid fighting in its wars.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.81,0:07:34.63,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,But it wouldn't be a good idea for either side
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.63,0:07:37.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to hand over its soldiers easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.38,0:07:41.02,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,We'll need to do this properly, you're saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.29,0:07:45.77,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, and for that, I'd like us to \Nagree on something in advance.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.59,0:07:48.43,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Another of your plans?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.43,0:07:50.03,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Way to go, villain in glasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.50,0:07:53.11,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,It's nothing that special.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.78,0:07:57.87,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I think we three should decide \Nour roles in advance.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.80,0:08:01.37,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Our roles, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.65,0:08:08.38,Default - italics,R,0000,0000,0000,,The goblin attack...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.81,0:08:11.88,Default - italics,R,0000,0000,0000,,I've never seen Father look so serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.65,0:08:15.18,Default - italics,R,0000,0000,0000,,How intense will the fighting be?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.60,0:08:17.89,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,It'll have to be Tsukuba.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.20,0:08:20.25,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,It's well defended,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.25,0:08:22.94,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,and should last a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.94,0:08:25.15,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,But who will tell Lord Kiliva?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.50,0:08:28.15,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,He'll lose more than a few \Nfields and outlying villages.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.15,0:08:30.58,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,In the worst case, most of the population.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.29,0:08:37.63,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure everyone is thinking \Nin the back of their minds
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.63,0:08:40.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that asking the adventurers \Nwould be the right move.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.01,0:08:44.67,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Yes... If they die, they return to life.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.04,0:08:48.64,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,But that would mean owing them a large debt.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.64,0:08:51.71,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,Which is why we avoid showing \Nthem our vulnerability,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.71,0:08:54.67,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,while getting information from \Nthem by any means necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.08,0:08:59.68,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,And they cannot learn that the Izumo \NKnights are gone, no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.31,0:09:03.32,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,Ultimately, we know nothing about them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.32,0:09:06.78,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,We need them to be our shield, \Neven if it means lying to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.43,0:09:11.83,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,They've finally called us?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.83,0:09:14.95,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,I hear the West Wind Brigade has arrived, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.16,0:09:17.70,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, they just contacted me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.20,0:09:22.20,Default,So,0000,0000,0000,,It's huge.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.68,0:09:26.22,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,They'll have to wait until the conference ends...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.84,0:09:30.09,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,Well, if it isn't...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.96,0:09:33.38,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Um—
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.38,0:09:34.80,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,Is something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.81,0:09:38.55,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,I'd imagined you'd be asleep in \Nyour soft bed at this hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.95,0:09:43.78,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,It's true that you may
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.78,0:09:47.56,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,see me as nothing but a lazy, cowardly girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.56,0:09:50.60,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,But I am also a member of the duke's family.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.60,0:09:52.44,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,There are nights when I'm too worried to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.73,0:09:54.07,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,I apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.51,0:09:55.37,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.12,0:09:58.82,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,You seemed to have something you wanted to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.56,0:10:07.64,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you say that freedom requires resolve?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.64,0:10:08.47,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.93,0:10:10.83,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't forgotten those words.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.05,0:10:13.55,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,That's all I wanted to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.81,0:10:22.96,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, we're all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.42,0:10:26.69,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,I think we've wiped out all \Nthe enemies in this area.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.69,0:10:28.64,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,We're resting now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.77,0:10:31.77,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Proceeding north-northwest, yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.32,0:10:33.26,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.26,0:10:34.49,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Three kilometers or so.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.90,0:10:36.15,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.15,0:10:39.03,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,You and Nyanta both be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.51,0:10:44.26,Default - flashback,R,0000,0000,0000,,Mage's Gauntlets?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.26,0:10:45.25,Default - flashback,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.25,0:10:47.92,Default - flashback,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Nyanta identified them for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.92,0:10:51.63,Default - flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,They're an item for magical attackers.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.63,0:10:54.50,Default - flashback,Se,0000,0000,0000,,As long as you're above level 25, \Nyou can equip them.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.50,0:10:55.76,Default - flashback,T,0000,0000,0000,,Level 25?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.76,0:10:58.27,Default - flashback,T,0000,0000,0000,,Then they can't be that great...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.27,0:11:02.48,Default - flashback,Se,0000,0000,0000,,But they're the first item we \Nacquired by working together.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.31,0:11:04.10,Default - flashback,I,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.48,0:11:07.99,Default - flashback,I,0000,0000,0000,,We worked together in Lagranda \NForest to get them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.99,0:11:10.10,Default - flashback,I,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't that make them an amazing treasure?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.39,0:11:12.08,Default - flashback,R,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.66,0:11:14.20,Default - flashback,T,0000,0000,0000,,But what do we do with them?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.20,0:11:16.66,Default - flashback,T,0000,0000,0000,,We can't all use them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.42,0:11:19.86,Default - flashback,I,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.22,0:11:22.06,Default - flashback,I,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't we let Rudy use them?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.99,0:11:26.01,Default - flashback,I,0000,0000,0000,,You said it's an item for \Nmagical attackers, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.41,0:11:27.61,Default - flashback,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.61,0:11:30.76,Default - flashback,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Rudy's the only mage in our group.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.76,0:11:33.75,Default - flashback,R,0000,0000,0000,,Um, but something that important...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.75,0:11:35.91,Default - flashback,T,0000,0000,0000,,That isn't like you, Rudy!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.91,0:11:37.14,Default - flashback,T,0000,0000,0000,,Since when are you so modest?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.14,0:11:38.43,Default - flashback,R,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think I am?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.43,0:11:39.69,Default - flashback,R,0000,0000,0000,,B-But...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.69,0:11:42.43,Default - flashback,R,0000,0000,0000,,Well, are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.47,0:11:49.60,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,They look good on you, Rudy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.23,0:11:53.16,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Let's get going.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.16,0:11:57.04,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,We'll head down into the ravine, \Nkeeping watch as we move.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.04,0:11:57.69,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.12,0:12:01.45,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I swear by these gauntlets that \NI'll defeat even more next time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.73,0:12:03.70,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Don't get too fired up.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.70,0:12:05.95,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,What? Is it bad to be fired up?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.39,0:12:11.29,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,No, let's do our best!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.97,0:12:15.96,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,And so, for these reasons,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.64,0:12:20.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we lords of the Freedom Cities of Eastal feel
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.93,0:12:22.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that in this emergency situation...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.67,0:12:24.61,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, we aren't getting anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.61,0:12:27.89,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,They're probably waiting for us to say something.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.66,0:12:32.81,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,We both want more information about what \Nthe other's thinking, to gain an advantage.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.21,0:12:35.81,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,So we'll go with the plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.58,0:12:41.19,Default - flashback,S,0000,0000,0000,,I'll talk about agreeing to send troops, \Nto try and gain information.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.06,0:12:45.07,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,If this is how they want to play it, \Nthere's no need to hold back.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.71,0:12:50.54,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,If anyone knows the status of the \NIzumo Knights, please tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.05,0:12:55.21,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's even worse than I expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.21,0:13:00.71,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,It seems clear that, for some reason, \Nthe Izumo Knights won't be coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.62,0:13:05.22,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,We cannot bring the Izumo \NKnights into a war like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.43,0:13:08.75,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,I would rather ask the Akihabara Round Table.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.75,0:13:11.93,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,With Akihabara in danger, why do you not rise?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.93,0:13:14.53,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,You're asking us to send troops?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.53,0:13:16.48,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,W-Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.76,0:13:19.70,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,I'd thought the purpose of this \Nconference was to hear
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.70,0:13:21.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,each individual lord's thoughts...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.57,0:13:26.00,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Or did you simply hope to hear our opinions?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.91,0:13:31.04,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'd heard the Akihabara knights \Nwere unmatched in combat...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.22,0:13:36.46,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,If you're using "knights" to mean a \Nstanding force, ready for battle,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.94,0:13:41.88,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,neither Akihabara nor the Round \NTable has any such thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.24,0:13:45.22,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Then what are you adventurers good for?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.51,0:13:47.22,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.50,0:13:49.00,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,What else?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.00,0:13:52.21,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,The adventurers' abilities are \Na blessing from the gods!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.21,0:13:53.97,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,You have a duty to save the land!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.41,0:13:56.98,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,That's news to me...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.42,0:13:59.45,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,What nonsense is that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.45,0:14:01.01,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,You're invincible, immortal.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.01,0:14:05.65,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,And despite that, you would \Nabandon your duty to the land?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.65,0:14:07.04,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,You should be ashamed!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.80,0:14:09.95,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.26,0:14:16.42,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,First off, we are not citizens \Nof the Freedom Cities!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.42,0:14:20.51,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,That's why we weren't summoned \Nto the conference before.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.51,0:14:21.25,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Am I wrong?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.27,0:14:25.25,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what plot you've devised,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.25,0:14:28.01,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,but we have no obligation \Nto accede to your demands.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.56,0:14:31.45,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you agree, Baron Krendit?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.45,0:14:33.01,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Th-That isn't...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.33,0:14:37.00,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,We didn't mean... Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.75,0:14:44.02,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,We are most certainly not plotting \Nto get Akihabara to send troops.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.02,0:14:47.54,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Then it was Lord Kiliva's individual request
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.54,0:14:54.03,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,that Akihabara send troops, not the will \Nof the League of Freedom Cities?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.75,0:15:00.17,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Are you saying that I'm acting \Nfor my own benefit here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.81,0:15:02.98,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,It is not the will of the entire League.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.98,0:15:07.67,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,But it's also true that many of us \Nwithin the League feel that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.05,0:15:11.54,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,Or will the proud, mighty warriors of Akihabara
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.54,0:15:15.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,stand aside while Yamato faces its hour of peril?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.48,0:15:17.43,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,We are not pets...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.90,0:15:21.19,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,"You guys are immortal, so go \Nand kill the goblins for us"?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.62,0:15:26.06,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Anyone who believed that, and sent \Ntheir comrades to the battlefield
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.06,0:15:29.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,could never gain the people of Akihabara's trust!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.92,0:15:35.20,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Was that too much?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.43,0:15:39.37,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,The adventurers risk losing their memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.12,0:15:42.88,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Anyone would get mad about that, not just you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.88,0:15:45.88,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,And it's your job to oppose sending troops.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.61,0:15:47.38,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.36,0:15:49.88,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that may have been a bit much.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.45,0:15:52.84,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not sure where we go from here...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.49,0:16:05.77,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Lenessia...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.08,0:16:20.80,Default - italics,R,0000,0000,0000,,What... What am I doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.80,0:16:23.21,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,You're looking as beautiful as ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.21,0:16:25.90,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Like a fairy on a lake, on a moonlit night.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.68,0:16:29.67,Default - italics,R,0000,0000,0000,,I shouldn't have come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.18,0:16:31.45,Default - italics,R,0000,0000,0000,,I shouldn't have come.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.00,0:16:33.48,Default - italics,R,0000,0000,0000,,I shouldn't have come.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.95,0:16:38.53,Default - italics,R,0000,0000,0000,,I want to put on my flannel \Npajamas and go to bed...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.53,0:16:41.55,Default - italics,R,0000,0000,0000,,I want to put my face down on \Na cold table and lie there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.26,0:16:44.81,Default - italics,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,Are you not slacking off today?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.90,0:16:48.02,Default - italics,R,0000,0000,0000,,Did I imagine that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.02,0:16:49.50,Default - italics,R,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure I heard it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.50,0:16:52.02,Default - italics,R,0000,0000,0000,,No, it doesn't matter...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.02,0:16:54.74,Default - italics,R,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I want to slack off, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.10,0:16:58.74,Default,G,0000,0000,0000,,Lenessia...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.28,0:17:00.49,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Crusty...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.22,0:17:04.26,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Princess Lenessia?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.67,0:17:06.75,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I am going to Akihabara.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.03,0:17:08.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Accompany me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.53,0:17:13.80,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,To Akihabara? Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.80,0:17:15.47,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,To raise an army of volunteers.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.02,0:17:18.71,Default - italics,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Impossible... What can a single woman do?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.71,0:17:21.76,Default - italics,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Speaking to a foreign band of \Nknights without permission?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.76,0:17:23.99,Default - italics,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,That far exceeds her authority...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.99,0:17:28.35,Default - italics,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,No, the Round Table's representative \Nis going with her...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.35,0:17:30.65,Default - italics,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,That could change things.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.84,0:17:34.11,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure that's likely to be a lot of work.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.11,0:17:34.93,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.93,0:17:36.66,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,Then why?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.91,0:17:40.80,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,You said that adventurers were free.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.55,0:17:46.67,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just a stupid girl, so I don't \Nreally understand politics.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.01,0:17:50.49,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,But I think that when you ask \Nsomeone for something,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.49,0:17:52.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you should show respect.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.22,0:17:54.08,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,As a member of the duke's family,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.08,0:17:56.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that's what my father and \Ngrandfather taught me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.29,0:17:57.18,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,That's why
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.56,0:18:00.23,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think we should be \Nhiding things from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.65,0:18:03.68,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Including the fact that the \NIzumo Knights are missing!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.06,0:18:06.25,Default,Guys,0000,0000,0000,,What has she done?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.25,0:18:07.73,Default,Guys,0000,0000,0000,,She's told them our secret!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.73,0:18:10.32,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,Well, now you've done it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.68,0:18:13.78,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,When I take responsibility, apologize with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.44,0:18:17.66,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,And, exactly what are you planning?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.66,0:18:20.41,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I see there are things even you don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.96,0:18:21.95,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.62,0:18:24.91,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have any plan at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.68,0:18:26.33,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.93,0:18:31.59,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,As a member of the Cowen family, \NI do not wish to be insulting.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.64,0:18:35.85,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Grandfather...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.46,0:18:37.86,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Continue.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.32,0:18:41.28,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Adventurers are free.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.28,0:18:44.03,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,They are more free than we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.03,0:18:47.78,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,It's true that we may be weaker than they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.78,0:18:50.90,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,But that doesn't mean that, in our weakness, \Nwe can become aggressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.43,0:18:54.16,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,We don't have the right to take advantage
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.16,0:18:57.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,of our weakness and use them as tools!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.78,0:19:02.91,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I shall go to Akihabara, and ask \Nthe adventurers directly.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.22,0:19:06.67,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Crusty said that adventurers are free.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.67,0:19:09.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So if any of them will agree to help us,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.82,0:19:11.67,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,why would we stop them?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.17,0:19:16.67,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I shall find even ten or fifteen \Nthat will agree to help us.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.06,0:19:20.87,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I learned from my grandfather \Nthat showing respect
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.87,0:19:22.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,doesn't mean using fancy words.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.12,0:19:25.53,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go there myself, to stand in the street,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.53,0:19:29.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and speak to each adventurer individually!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.62,0:19:35.62,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Princess Lenessia!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.62,0:19:36.97,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.97,0:19:38.72,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,She was just very nervous.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.27,0:19:41.03,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,Can I leave the rest of this to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.53,0:19:44.42,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't. That would be a waste.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.42,0:19:45.78,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,So what will you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.90,0:19:49.57,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Will you accept her resolve, or not?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.57,0:19:52.36,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,The final decision lies with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.69,0:20:04.86,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,A bird?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.87,0:20:10.52,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,It's scary out here at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.52,0:20:12.73,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,There are probably all kinds \Nof enemies still out here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.33,0:20:14.51,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,It's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.51,0:20:17.99,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,We've only defeated a tiny \Npercentage of the goblins.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.28,0:20:21.36,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how many we kill, it may not matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.83,0:20:24.06,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,It's even scarier when the fighting starts.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.06,0:20:26.72,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,You can trip on roots and soft ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.72,0:20:29.37,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, you lose your balance easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.37,0:20:33.16,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,I'm always anxious because I never know \Nwhen the enemy will appear.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.16,0:20:35.95,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe it's because you're \Non higher alert at night...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.95,0:20:37.71,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Like for the scent of the monsters.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.71,0:20:38.67,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.67,0:20:41.16,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I hate that scent.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.70,0:20:42.71,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.66,0:20:45.65,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay to do our best!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.65,0:20:47.27,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay for us to try and save them!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.27,0:20:49.31,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, it's just fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.31,0:20:50.93,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.35,0:20:55.65,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,If you'd leave behind people in trouble, \Nhow can you be an adventurer?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.50,0:20:57.87,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,That's right...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.87,0:21:00.47,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,We don't need to think about anything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.88,0:21:03.50,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,We'll all protect the people we care about.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.50,0:21:05.20,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,That's all there is to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.62,0:21:08.62,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,And as a shrine priestess,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.98,0:21:11.75,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,my job is to keep us all safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.19,0:21:21.34,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you laughing, my lord?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.34,0:21:24.05,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I've never seen Crusty looking like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.61,0:21:26.80,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,He was totally overwhelmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.13,0:21:29.40,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,That princess impresses me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.40,0:21:31.31,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't expect her to do that there.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.20,0:21:33.34,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,It's about respect, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.34,0:21:34.45,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Respect?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.45,0:21:35.50,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.50,0:21:38.44,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Even if the Round Table promised to send troops,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.44,0:21:40.94,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,it wouldn't mean Akihabara would act.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.58,0:21:44.56,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Because, as she said, adventurers are free.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.42,0:21:49.98,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,If you want them to act, you need \Nto persuade each one individually.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.49,0:21:54.23,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,And she seemed to understand that perfectly.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.23,0:21:57.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She said she'd do all she could to \Nshow respect at that meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.57,0:22:01.01,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,But in a way, isn't that obvious?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.01,0:22:03.80,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.80,0:22:06.85,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,But everyone there was about to ignore it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.86,0:22:09.23,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Including us.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.53,0:22:13.94,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,What's that light?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.94,0:22:15.34,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,The city of Akihabara.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.09,0:22:18.23,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,It's night...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.85,0:22:20.42,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,But the light is so warm...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.64,0:22:29.49,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,She may be the one who saves the Freedom \NCities of Eastal from the dead end
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.49,0:22:31.80,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,in which they've found themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.02,0:22:35.26,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,That lazy, cowardly princess...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.77,0:24:08.46,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,She finds herself in a town she doesn't know
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.46,0:24:09.70,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,with things she's never seen,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.70,0:24:10.97,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,things she's never heard,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.97,0:24:12.80,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,and people she's never met.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.80,0:24:16.01,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,She learns how big the world is, \Nand how tiny she is.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.47,0:24:19.41,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,She cries out her resolve and her hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.79,0:24:22.84,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,And her words drive the adventurers to action.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.23,0:24:30.99,Title,,0000,0000,0000,,Expeditionary Force
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.41,0:24:25.36,Default,Next time,0000,0000,0000,,Next time: Expeditionary Force.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.36,0:24:28.00,Default,Next time,0000,0000,0000,,Always look thirty seconds ahead.
